<!-- CART CREATE -->
                    <div class="documentation">
                        <h3>POST /carts</h3>
                        <p class="lead">Creates a new CART. On the creation, the items array can be empty (eg. <code>items:[]</code>) </p>
                        <pre><code class="http">POST http://api.marketcloud.it/v0/carts</code></pre>
                        <h5>Parameters</h5>
                        <div class="table-responsive"><table class="table table-striped documentation">
                            <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>user_id</td>
                                    <td>Number</td>
                                    <td>The univocal user identifier</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>items <span class="label label-success">Required</span></td>
                                    <td>Array of Object</td>
                                    <td>The list of items, in the form <code>{product_id:1,quantity:10}</code>, added on the cart</td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table></div>
                        
                        
                        <h5>Example Request</h5>
                        <iframe src="//api.apiembed.com/?source=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Marketcloud/json-request-examples/master/carts/update.json&targets=shell:curl,java:unirest,python:requests,ruby:native,objc:nsurlsession,go:native,csharp:restsharp" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" width="100%" height="300px" seamless></iframe>
                        <h5>Example JSON response (200)</h5>
                        <pre><code class="javascript">
{
    status:true,
    data: {
        id:3,
        user_id:1
        items: [
        {
          product_id:13,
          quantity:2
        },{
          product_id:15,
          quantity:3
        }]
    }
    
}</code></pre>
<h5>Working with variants</h5>
<p>In order to add to a cart a product with variants, we must specify which variant we are adding to the cart:</p>
<pre><code class="javascript">
{ "product_id" : 1111, "quantity" : 1, "variant_id" : 2 }
</code></pre>           
